              <Comments>In a number of languages, it is possible to reflect something of the figurative meaning of {L:παγίς&lt;SDBG:παγίς:000000&gt;} by translating the term as a verb, for example, ‘may they be caught and trapped at their feasts’ or ‘may their feasts snare and trap them’ (see {D:6.23} and {D:6.24}).</Comments>
